(8344, 646, 'my_money_3_image_content_content_description', 'Business owners must provide valid identification, business permits, and financial records. Additional documentation may be necessary depending on the loan type and amount.\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>\r\n<h3>Employed individuals</h3>\r\nSubmit a valid ID, proof of income, and Certificate of Employment. Bank statements may be required to verify financial stability.</li>\r\n 	<li>\r\n<h3>Self-employed individuals</h3>\r\nProvide business registration, financial statements, and proof of earnings. Bank records may also be needed.</li>\r\n 	<li>\r\n<h3>Overseas Filipino Workers (OFWs)</h3>\r\nPresent a valid passport, employment contract, and proof of remittance. An SPA may be necessary for applications filed through a representative.</li>\r\n 	<li>\r\n<h3>Corporations or partnerships</h3>\r\nSubmit company registration documents, financial records, and proof of business operations. A board resolution authorizing the loan application may be required.</li>\r\n</ol>');
