(8917, 820, 'my_money_3_image_content_content_description', 'A microfinance loan typically requires valid identification, proof of income, and supporting business documents. Additional paperwork may be necessary depending on the loan amount and borrower’s financial status.\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>\r\n<h3>Employed individuals</h3>\r\nProvide valid identification, proof of income, and employment verification documents. Bank records may be requested for higher loan amounts.</li>\r\n 	<li>\r\n<h3>Self-employed individuals</h3>\r\nSubmit business permits, proof of earnings, and financial records. Other supporting documents may be required based on loan amount.</li>\r\n 	<li>\r\n<h3>Overseas Filipino Workers (OFWs)</h3>\r\nPresent a valid passport, proof of remittance, and employment contract. An SPA may be necessary for applications filed through a representative.</li>\r\n 	<li>\r\n<h3>Corporations or partnerships</h3>\r\nProvide business registration, latest financial statements, and proof of business operations. An authorization letter from company officials may be required.</li>\r\n</ol>'),
