(11662, 504, 'my_money_3_image_content_content_description', 'To apply for a motorcycle loan, you will need valid identification, proof of income, and other supporting documents. Requirements may vary depending on your employment status and loan amount.\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>\r\n<h3>Employed individuals</h3>\r\nSubmit a valid government-issued ID, latest payslips, and Certificate of Employment to verify your financial capability. Additional documents may be requested based on your employer and loan amount.</li>\r\n 	<li>\r\n<h3>Self-employed individuals</h3>\r\nProvide a valid ID, business registration documents, and latest financial statements or bank statements. Other supporting documents may be needed to assess your income stability.</li>\r\n 	<li>\r\n<h3>Overseas Filipino Workers (OFWs)</h3>\r\nPresent a valid passport, proof of remittance, and a contract of employment. Additional requirements may include an affidavit of support or a Special Power of Attorney (SPA).</li>\r\n 	<li>\r\n<h3>Corporations or partnerships</h3>\r\nSubmit company registration documents, latest financial statements, and proof of business operations. The company’s authorized signatory must also provide valid identification and a board resolution, if applicable.</li>\r\n</ol>'),
