(11806, 495, 'my_money_3_image_content_content_description', 'A housing loan application typically requires valid IDs, proof of income, and property-related documents. Additional paperwork may be necessary based on the type of loan and borrower profile.\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>\r\n<h3>Employed individuals</h3>\r\nProvide a valid ID, latest income documents, and Certificate of Employment. Proof of billing and marriage certificate (if applicable) may also be required.</li>\r\n 	<li>\r\n<h3>Self-employed individuals</h3>\r\nSubmit business registration documents, latest financial statements, and proof of business operations. A list of major clients or contracts may be required to verify income sources.</li>\r\n 	<li>\r\n<h3>Overseas Filipino Workers (OFWs)</h3>\r\nPresent a valid passport, employment contract, and remittance slips. A Special Power of Attorney (SPA) may be needed if the borrower is applying while abroad.</li>\r\n 	<li>\r\n<h3>Corporations or partnerships</h3>\r\nProvide business permits, latest audited financial statements, and proof of company ownership. A board resolution authorizing the loan application is also required.</li>\r\n</ol>'),
