(1015, 1, '2025-03-03 07:57:15', '2025-03-03 07:57:15', 'Banking institutions have started migrating to the EuroPay, MasterCard and Visa (EMV) chip technology, in compliance with Circular 859 from the Bangko Sentral ng Pilipinas that mandates the migration for all debit and credit card-issuing companies by January 2017.\r\n\r\nThe EMV-chip based payment card is recognized as more secure alternative to traditional magnetic stripe payment cards. Its “dynamic authentication” feature, which generates a unique transaction code, protects data against counterfeit fraud, skimming and other related attacks perpetrated on magnetic stripe payment cards. Read more about EMV and the ongoing migration here.', 'EMV Migration - FAQs', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'emv-migration-faqs', '', '', '2025-03-03 07:57:15', '2025-03-03 07:57:15', '', 0, 'https://bankofmakati.innovnational.com/?post_type=news&#038;p=1015', 8, 'news', '', 0),
(1016, 1, '2025-03-03 07:58:25', '2025-03-03 07:58:25', '<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1017\" src=\"https://bankofmakati.innovnational.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/La-Union-Branch-Opening2-scaled.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1978\" />\r\n\r\nBank of Makati continues to expand its reach with the inauguration of the La Union branch, its 57th nationwide.\r\n\r\nThe La Union branch is the 19th to be inaugurated this year, following the launch of branches in Biñan (Laguna), Muntinlupa, Baliuag (Bulacan), Valenzuela, Las Piñas, Rodriguez (Rizal), Daet (Camarines Norte), Tagum (Davao), Pagadian City (Zamboanga del Sur), Calapan City (Oriental Mindoro), Butuan City (Agusan del Norte), Valencia (Bukidnon), Lucena (Quezon), Zamboanga, Balanga (Bataan), Urdaneta (Pangasinan), Buendia (Makati) and Gensan (South Cotabato).\r\n\r\nLeading the simple inauguration rites last October 18, 2016 were BMI President Ma. Rodora E. Bañares and Atty. Nancy Lopez Bilaoen of Office of the La Union Vice Mayor as guest.\r\nThe La Union branch is manned by Ramoncito P. Boton (Branch Operations Officer), Gideon L. Dela Cruz and Rodalyn A. Galleste (Branch Relationship Officers), Rosalinda F. Javier (Loan Coordinator), Mark Paul P. Alvarez (Roving Teller) and Catherine O. Sabando (Account Officer).\r\n\r\nThe branch is located at Nera Building, Quezon Avenue San Fernando, La Union, with phone numbers 0943-598-2208 / 0922-802-9792.', 'BMI La Union becomes 57th branch', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'bmi-la-union-becomes-57th-branch-8', '', '', '2025-03-03 07:58:25', '2025-03-03 07:58:25', '', 0, 'https://bankofmakati.innovnational.com/?post_type=news&#038;p=1016', 7, 'news', '', 0),
