share with our third-party service provider such as collection agency; and\r\n    <br />• To ensure safety and security.\r\n</p>\r\n<h2>How We Use Your Personal Information</h2>\r\n<p>We use personal data collected to:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Deliver and provide the products and services that you avail, such as to process applications and transactions\r\n        for loans and deposits, respond to queries, requests and complaints and to improve how we interact with you;\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>Send you statements, billings, notices and other such documents necessary for continued use of our products and\r\n        services;</li>\r\n    <li>Conduct studies and researches to develop new products or to improve our existing products and services;</li>\r\n    <li>Perform profile analysis, modeling and analytics to better understand needs, preferences and market trends for\r\n        the development of more suitable products and services;</li>\r\n    <li>Reach out to you regarding products and services information, including offers, promotions, discounts, rewards;\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>Know your experience with us thru our various touchpoints such as branches, call center, telemarketing, email,\r\n        messaging and other channels;</li>\r\n    <li>Determine the effectiveness and sufficiency of our marketing efforts and initiatives;</li>\r\n    <li>Provide location-based services such as finding the nearest ATM or branch to you, as well as extending out our\r\n        other services to you;</li>\r\n    <li>Perform certain protective safeguards against improper use or abuse of our products and services including fraud\r\n        prevention;</li>\r\n    <li>Comply with our operational, audit, administrative, credit and risk management processes, policies and\r\n        procedures, the terms and conditions governing our products, services, facilities and</li>\r\n    <li>channels, the Bangko Sentral ng Pilipinas rules and regulations, legal and regulatory requirements of government\r\n        regulators, judicial, supervisory bodies, tax authorities or courts of</li>\r\n    <li>competent jurisdiction, as the same may be amended or supplemented from time to time</li>\r\n    <li>Comply with applicable laws of the Philippines and those of other jurisdictions to which the Bank has legal or\r\n        contractual obligation to comply, the laws on the prevention of money</li>\r\n    <li>laundering, terrorist financing and proliferation financing such as the provisions of Republic Act No. 9160\r\n        (Anti-Money Laundering Act of 2001), as amended, and the implementation of</li>\r\n    <li>know-your- customer and sanction screening checks;</li>\r\n    <li>Comply with legal and regulatory requirements such as submission of data to credit bureaus, credit information\r\n        companies, the Credit Information Corporation (CIC) (pursuant to RA No.</li>\r\n    <li>9510 and its implementing rules and regulations), responding to court orders and other instructions and requests\r\n        from any local or foreign authorities including regulatory, governmental, tax</li>\r\n    <li>and law enforcement authorities or other similar authorities, and</li>\r\n    <li>Perform other activities permitted by law or with your consent.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>How Long Do We Keep Your Personal Data</h2>\r\n<p>Personal data will not be retained by the Bank longer than necessary. The minimum retention period is five (5) years\r\n    because we adhere to the applicable laws and regulations, such as BSP Circular No. 720 and Republic Act No. 9160\r\n    (Anti-Money Laundering Act of 2001), as amended.</p>\r\n<h2>How We Store Your Personal Data</h2>\r\n<p>It is our practice that all documents must be inventoried and classified according to the Bank\'s protection of the\r\n    records and information security classification. We determine the storage requirements of every document either\r\n    stored in permanent vault or in a non-fire resistant cabinet in a fire-rated environment, whichever is necessary.\r\n    <br /><br />We also determine our records that should remain in the respective department and those records that\r\n    will be forwarded to our warehouse for safekeeping.\r\n</p>\r\n<h2>How We Dispose Your Personal Data</h2>\r\n<p>Any records that have passed the useful life and no longer have any legal need to be retained must be safely and\r\n    systematically disposed. The Bank\'s Records Management Unit (RMU) prompts the concerned department\'s records\r\n    management officer (RMO) on the files due for destruction. <br /><br />Methods of Destruction:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Paper\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li>Shredding</li>\r\n            <li>Pulping</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </li>\r\n    <li>Electronic records <br />\r\n        <ul>\r\n            <li>Hard drives should be re-formatted when computers are disposed;</li>\r\n            <li>Deleted emails from inboxes, sent items and deleted items boxes, records may still be accessible on\r\n                back-up servers;</li>\r\n            <li>Magnetic media such as magnetic tape, other computer storage mechanisms should be subjected to the force\r\n                of a strong magnetic field; and</li>\r\n            <li>Other machine-readable devices can be cut or shredded</li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n    </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Your Rights as Data Subjects</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><strong>Right to Be Informed</strong>: You have the right to be informed as stated under the Data Privacy Act of\r\n        2012. In connection with this, we have this privacy statement posted at our website and privacy notices posted\r\n        in every branch of the Bank;</li>\r\n    <li><strong>Right to Access</strong>: You have the right to access your personal data disclosed to us by reaching\r\n        out to our Customer Experience Management Department through this e-mail address\r\n        malalapitan.kaibigan@bankofmakati.com.ph in accordance with procedure prescribed by the Bank;</li>\r\n    <li><strong>Right to Objec</strong>t: You have the right to object if we process your personal data without lawful\r\n        basis enumerated under Sections 12 and 13 of the Data Privacy Act of 2012;</li>\r\n    <li><strong>Right to Erase</strong> or Block: You have the right to request the erasure or blocking of personal\r\n        information if we process your personal data without lawful basis under Sections 12 and 13 of the Data Privacy\r\n        Act of 2012;</li>\r\n    <li><strong>Right to Correct or Rectify</strong>: You have the right to request correction of wrong personal\r\n        information in our possession and we reserve the right to request proof or evidence to verify the correctness of\r\n        your information;</li>\r\n    <li><strong>Right to File a Complaint and Right to Damages</strong>: If after you have raised a concern with us and\r\n        we failed to address your concern, you have the right to file a complaint with the National Privacy Commission\r\n        through their website privacy.gov.ph. If warranted, we will indemnify subject to what is due and ordered by the\r\n        National Privacy Commission;</li>\r\n    <li>In case your rights under the Data Privacy Act of 2012 are violated, you may send us an email through our\r\n        privacy concern email address privacyconcern@bankofmakati.com.ph, and give us a chance to correct the possible\r\n        violation.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>How We Protect Your Personal Information</h2>\r\n<p>Our technology and information security framework, which undergoes continuous assessment to improve in securing your\r\n    privacy, shall prevent unauthorized access to your information. <br /><br />Our oversight risk management\r\n    department, monitors the risk appetite of the Bank to ensure that we are in compliance with the regulators and does\r\n    not violate the rights of clients.</p>\r\n<div class=\"row align-items-center\">\r\n    <div class=\"col-lg-6\">\r\n        <div class=\"content\">\r\n            <h2>Contact Our Data Protection Officer (DPO)</h2>\r\n            <p>For any privacy concern, you may reach our Data Protection Officer through the following\r\n                means:<br /><br /><strong>Email</strong>:\r\n                privacyconcern@bankofmakati.com.ph<br /><strong>Contact</strong> No: 8889-0000 loc. 1113 or 1601\r\n                09255-256683<br /><strong>Address</strong>: The Data Protection Officer – Bank of Makati (A Savings\r\n                Bank), Inc. Bank of Makati Bldg. Ayala Ave Extension near cor Metropolitan Ave, Brgy. Bel-air, Makati\r\n                City</p>\r\n        </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n    <div class=\"col-lg-6\">\r\n        <div class=\"image\">\r\n            <img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-1156\"\r\n                src=\"https://bankofmakati.innovnational.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/dpo.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"380\"\r\n                height=\"700\" />\r\n        </div>\r\n    </div>\r\n</div>', 'Data Privacy Statement', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '3-revision-v1', '', '', '2025-06-20 01:44:31', '2025-06-20 01:44:31', '', 3, 'https://bankofmakati.innovnational.com/?p=1158', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
