 data will not be retained by the Bank longer than necessary. The minimum retention period is five (5)\r\n        yearsbecause we adhere to the applicable laws and regulations, such as BSP Circular No. 720 and Republic Act No.\r\n        9160(Anti-Money Laundering Act of 2001), as amended.</p>\r\n    <h2>How We Store Your Personal Data</h2>\r\n    <p>It is our practice that all documents must be inventoried and classified according to the Bank’s protection of\r\n        therecords and information security classification. We determine the storage requirements of every document\r\n        either storedin permanent vault or in a non-fire resistant cabinet in a fire-rated environment, whichever is\r\n        necessary.</p>\r\n    <p>We also determine our records that should remain in the respective department and those records that will be\r\n        forwarded to ourwarehouse for safekeeping.</p>\r\n    <h2>How We Dispose Your Personal Data</h2>\r\n    <p>Any records that have passed the useful life and no longer have any legal need to be retained must be safely\r\n        andsystematically disposed. The Bank’s Records Management Unit (RMU) prompts the concerned department’s records\r\n        managementofficer (RMO) on the files due for destruction. Methods of Destruction:</p>\r\n    <ol style=\"list-style-type: lower-alpha;\">\r\n        <li>Paper<ul>\r\n                <li>Shredding</li>\r\n                <li>Pulping</li>\r\n            </ul>\r\n        </li>\r\n        <li>Electronic records<ul>\r\n                <li>Hard drives should be re-formatted when computers are disposed;</li>\r\n                <li>Deleted emails from inboxes, sent items and deleted items boxes, records may still be accessible\r\n                    onback-up servers;</li>\r\n                <li>Magnetic media such as magnetic tape, other computer storage mechanisms should be subjected to the\r\n                    forceof a strong magnetic field; and</li>\r\n                <li>Other machine-readable devices can be cut or shredded</li>\r\n            </ul>\r\n        </li>\r\n    </ol>\r\n    <h2>Your Rights as Data Subjects</h2>\r\n    <ul>\r\n        <li><strong>Right to Be Informed</strong>: You have the right to be informed as stated under the Data Privacy\r\n            Act of2012. In connection with this, we have this privacy statement posted at our website and privacy\r\n            notices postedin every branch of the Bank;</li>\r\n        <li><strong>Right to Access</strong>: You have the right to access your personal data disclosed to us by\r\n            reachingout to our Customer Experience Management Department through this e-mail\r\n            addressmalalapitan.kaibigan@bankofmakati.com.ph in accordance with procedure prescribed by the Bank;</li>\r\n        <li><strong>Right to Object</strong>: You have the right to object if we process your personal data without\r\n            lawfulbasis enumerated under Sections 12 and 13 of the Data Privacy Act of 2012;</li>\r\n        <li><strong>Right to Erase or Block</strong>: You have the right to request the erasure or blocking of\r\n            personalinformation if we process your personal data without lawful basis under Sections 12 and 13 of the\r\n            Data PrivacyAct of 2012;</li>\r\n        <li><strong>Right to Correct or Rectify</strong>: You have the right to request correction of wrong\r\n            personalinformation in our possession and we reserve the right to request proof or evidence to verify the\r\n            correctness ofyour information;</li>\r\n        <li><strong>Right to File a Complaint and Right to Damages</strong>: If after you have raised a concern with us\r\n            andwe failed to address your concern, you have the right to file a complaint with the National Privacy\r\n            Commissionthrough their website privacy.gov.ph. If warranted, we will indemnify subject to what is due and\r\n            ordered by theNational Privacy Commission;</li